cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with learning representations of entities and relations in temporal knowledge graphs using recurrent neural networks. This involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for learning latent representations, as well as methods from databases (cs.DB) for handling temporal data. The use of recurrent neural networks also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) where these models are commonly used.
